definitions.definition: A town in Epsom and Ewell borough , Surrey , England , known for its racecourse ( OS grid ref TQ2060 ) .
An unincorporated community in Bogard Township, Daviess County , Indiana , United States ; the well water tasted of Epsom salts .
A town in Merrimack County , New Hampshire , United States , named after Epsom, Surrey.
A rural locality in Isaac Region, Queensland , Australia .
A suburb of Bendigo in the City of Greater Bendigo , Victoria , Australia .
A suburb of Auckland , New Zealand .
